issue.body:
[Exercise 2.5 (e)](https://github.com/dabeaz-course/python-mastery/blob/main/Exercises/ex2_5.md?plain=1#L286) asks:

> What happens when you take a slice of ride data?

The solution presented only covers (c) and (d). I don't know if the solution to (e) was intentionally left out - in case it wasn't, here's my solution.

commits.message:
Update ex6_2.md to fix variable mismatch

The sell() method takes the nshares argument, however inside the method the variable shares is used instead.

This patch changes the name of the argument according to the variable used within the method.
